	<h2>Signs Your Fence Is Nearing End of Life</h2>

	<h3>Wood Fence End-of-Life Indicators</h3>
	<p>Warning signs replacement is approaching:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Widespread rot:</strong> More than 30% of boards showing soft spots or decay</li>
		<li><strong>Multiple leaning posts:</strong> 4+ posts loose or leaning indicates systemic failure</li>
		<li><strong>Extensive cracking:</strong> Deep cracks in majority of boards</li>
		<li><strong>Warping/twisting:</strong> Boards severely warped creating gaps and weak points</li>
		<li><strong>Failed repairs:</strong> Previous repairs failing within 1-2 years</li>
		<li><strong>Post rot below ground:</strong> Posts breaking off at ground level</li>
		<li><strong>Age factor:</strong> Fence approaching 75%+ of expected lifespan for material</li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Vinyl Fence End-of-Life Indicators</h3>
	<p>Signs vinyl fence is failing:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Brittleness:</strong> Panels crack easily when stressed or impacted</li>
		<li><strong>Severe discoloration:</strong> Heavy fading, yellowing, or chalking</li>
		<li><strong>Panel cracking:</strong> Stress cracks developing in multiple panels</li>
		<li><strong>Hardware failure:</strong> Brackets, caps breaking due to material degradation</li>
		<li><strong>Unavailable parts:</strong> Replacement sections no longer manufactured</li>
	</ul>

